  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n\r\n  \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">BASIC ECONOMIC PROBLEM<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">An economic system is an arrangement specifying how production and consumption are controlled in a society. Examples of different economic systems are capitalism, socialism and mixed economy.<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The society must make choice from the scarce resources which, have alternative uses. The problem of scarcity brings economic problems of the society.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The basic economic problems include<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">What to produce?<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">How to produce?<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">For whom to produce?<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Efficiency of resource use<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">How much to consume and save?<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What to produce?<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What to produce primarily depends on consumers in free market. The consumers choose the product they like and thus their choices direct the types of production that should be carried out. The firms will follow this because this is the most profit maximizing combination.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Sometimes the government too can decide what to produce. The government may decide to produce an essential good or service which everyone ought to have.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How to produce?<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">This question will be answered by those supplying the goods and services. If the supplier is a private firm, it will seek to use the method which will give the maximum profit. For example, production can be done using labour intensive method and capital-intensive method. The private firm will decide on the method which will give lowest average costs.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">If the government is the supplier, it may try to use the method which promotes welfare of the society rather than maximising the profit.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">For whom to produce?<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">For whom to produce will also depend on the suppliers (government and private firms). The consumers are the target of production, but the kind of consumers the firm or the government wants to target is the question. The government usually produces for the general public where as the private firms can seek to maximize profit by producing for the high and rich level customers as well as the general public. In simple words, the production is done for those who are willing to pay.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Note: among the suppliers, there will also be private individuals (sole traders). Their objective in production is the same as that of the private firms &ndash; that is, to maximise profit.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Efficiency of resources use&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">It is a fact that resources are scarce and as a result, all the available resources should be used without allowing anyone to lie idle. This is the problem of getting the best result from any approach we adopt in employing our scarce resources (that is technical efficiency). If all the resources are used, maximum output will be produced and this can only be achieved through the use technical efficiency.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How much to commit? and save?&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In the society, all the outputs produced are not to be consumed. Some could be kept for future consumption or for export which will generate some funds to the society. This fund can later be used for further production of goods and services.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Different economic system<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">This includes;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">capitalism, socialism and mixed economy&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Capitalism is an economic system that allows private ownership of property or means of production and distribution. This is also called market economy.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Socialism refers to economic system in which the state owns and controls the means of production and distribution.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Mixed Economy is an economic system where both the private individuals and the government are allowed to own and control the means of production and distribution.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How the basic problems are solved in a Capitalist or free market economy&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What to produce:<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The question as to what to produce and at What quantities in a free market economy is answered by the forces of demand and supply. Goods that use in high demand attract high prices and this encourages producers to produce more while goods that are in low demand attract low prices and this discourages production.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How to Produce:<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;In a free market system, where labour is cheap and available in abundance, a wise decision is to use a labour intensive method or to use a capital-intensive method where capital is relatively cheap.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">For whom to produce:<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;It is a question of how to distribute the goods produced Under a free market economy, it is decided by the forces of demand and supply.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Efficient use of resources:&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">This is the problem of getting the best result from any approach we adopt in employing our scarce resources. The problem is solved by application of technical efficiency which is making use of the best production method to produce the highest production level at the least possible cost.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How much to consume and save (for investment)?<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;In a free enterprise, all output produced are not to be consumed, some could be kept for future consumption or for export which will generate some funds for the society.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How the basic problems are solved in<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Socialist Economy<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What to Produce<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">: The decision of what to produce and at what quantities is carried out based on national priorities. The state estimates the needs of the people through its agencies.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How to Produce:&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The main objective in a socialist economy is to ensure full utilization of resources. The planning authority therefore, chooses a technique of production that is in line with this objective. For Whom to Produce: Production is controlled by the state or government. Therefore, goods are distributed equitably by government agencies according to the desires of the consumers.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How the basic problems are solved in a Mixed Economy&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">What to Produce:<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;What to produce by private sector is controlled by the market forces of demand and supply while the planning agency decides what to produce in the public sector and administer prices.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">How to Produce:<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;In the private sector, the profit motive of firms decides how to ptoduce. However, in the public sector, the decision is made on the basis of the welfare motive.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">For Whom to Produce:&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Some of the goods that are produced are distributed in the market on the basis of price mechanism while some are distributed by the government through the public distribution.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">NB:&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In capitalism, basic problems are solved through the price mechanism while in socialism the state solves the problems through its agencies.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">PUME Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In a market economy, the question of what, how and for whom to produce are solved by the ____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. elected representative of the people, B. planning committee<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. price mechanism, D. government<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2006\/2007, no 4).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">price mechanism<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A system in which the means of production is held in trust for the people by government is known as a ____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. social economy. B. capitalist economy. C. subsistence economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. mixed economy. E. open economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A (2011\/2012, no 9).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">social economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Socialism is an economic system in which part of the means of production and distribution are collectively owned and controlled by the government or state.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">JAMB Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">An economy in which both the public and private sectors contribute to economic growth is as<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. feudal economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. capitalist economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. socialist economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. mixed economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. mixed economy<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In capitalist economies, questions about what to produce are ultimately answered by<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. income level of households<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. available technical skills in the economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. output decisions of firms<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. holding decision of households<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. output decisions of firms<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In capitalist economies, questions about what to produce are ultimately answered by<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. income level of households<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. available technical skills in the economy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. output decisions of firms<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. holding decision of households<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. output decisions of firms<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In a free market economy, prices are determined by&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. consumers&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. producers&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. the central government&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. the forces of demand and supply.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. the forces of demand and supply.<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The basic economic problem of what to produce in an economy is determined by&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. the availability of labour&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. the means of distribution&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. the availability of resources&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. technological know-how.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. The availability of resources, Nigeria deals in oil because they have the raw material.<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Freedom of consumption and production are characteristics of&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. socialism&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. feudalism&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. capitalism&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. communism<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. capitalism&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The choice of how to produce in a command economy is determined by<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. government<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. consumer<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. industrialists<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. labour unions<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. government<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Freedom of consumption and production are characteristics of&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. socialism&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. feudalism&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. capitalism&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. communism<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. Feudalism<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "BASIC ECONOMIC PROBLEM"
}